250 g Ground Beef
1 unit(s) Sour Cream
2 unit(s) Green Onion
½ cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
1 unit(s) Hot Pepper
2 tbsp Tomato Sauce Base
8 g Enchilada Spice Blend
1 unit(s) Lettuce
1 unit(s) Black Beans
1.5 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, wash and dry all produce.
Cut ends off lettuce, then gently separate leaves. Rinse and dry leaves.
Thinly slice green onions.
Core, then cut hot pepper into 1/4-inch pieces.
Using a strainer, drain and rinse beans.

In a large non-stick pan, heat 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil over medium-high. When the pan is hot, add beef and Enchilada Spice Blend. Cook 3-5 min, breaking up beef into smaller pieces, until no pink remains.** Season with salt and pepper.
Using a slotted spoon, transfer mixture to a medium bowl, then cover to keep warm.

Add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil to the same pan (used in step 2), then peppers. Cook 3-4 min, stirring occasionally, until tender-crisp. Season with salt and pepper.
Add beef and beans to the pan.
Add tomato sauce base and 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) water. Cook 3-4 min, stirring often, until well-combined and beans are warmed through.

Divide beef-bean mixture between lettuce leaves.
Top with cheese, then green onions.
Dollop sour cream over top.

Divide lettuce leaf tacos between plates.